		<article class="entry hentry author-jenny-lo post-type-text article-index-2" id="article-58d4749486e6c04becf4d007" data-item-id="58d4749486e6c04becf4d007">

			<p class="entry-categories">
				
			</p>
			<h1 data-content-field="title" class="entry-title">
				
					<a href="/teajournal/2017/3/23/renai-oollo-tea-subscription-march-2017">Ren'ai: Tea SUBSCRIPTION MARCH 2017 </a>
				
			</h1>

			<p class="entry-date-author">
				<span class="entry-author"><a href="/teajournal?author=54028563e4b09fa759f11482">Jenny Lo</a> · </span><time class="published" datetime="2017-03-23"><a href="/teajournal/2017/3/23/renai-oollo-tea-subscription-march-2017">March 23, 2017</a></time>
			</p>

			<div class="entry-content">
				
					
						<div class="sqs-layout sqs-grid-12 columns-12" data-layout-label="Post Body" data-type="item" data-updated-on="1490318749003" id="item-58d4749486e6c04becf4d007"><div class="row sqs-row"><div class="col sqs-col-12 span-12"><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html" data-block-type="2" id="block-2155a04b1380d2e4beba"><div class="sqs-block-content"><h3>Ren'ai:&nbsp;TEA SUBSCRIPTION MARCH 2017&nbsp;</h3><blockquote>“Meanwhile, let us have a sip of tea. The afternoon glow is brightening the bamboos, the fountains are bubbling with delight, the soughing of the pines is heard in our kettle. Let us dream of evanescence and linger in the beautiful foolishness of things.”&nbsp;<br />― Kakuzō Okakura, The Book of Tea</blockquote><p>March is a month of new beginnings, new life and the start of tea harvest season! We are discovering the relatively new tea farming region of Ren’ai Township, Nantou, Taiwan.&nbsp;</p></div></div><div class="sqs-block image-block sqs-block-image" data-block-type="5" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1490318458710_19129"><div class="sqs-block-content">








  

    
  
    <div
