            <noscript><img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/54028565e4b079634bac0558/1490305643087-S5RU5BHLNGP0BZZAZ6AH/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kPZjswWEEM1xUlE2nw_1gDZZw-zPPgdn4jUwVcJE1ZvWEtT5uBSRWt4vQZAgTJucoTqqXjS3CfNDSuuf31e0tVFEypcWtVdAnmHnO4a1hPNGKftICS8WvBaaDvL8dARr2lYCOBSuh7_iz0ZUXSA5sds/image-asset.jpeg" alt="" /></noscript><img class="thumb-image" data-src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/54028565e4b079634bac0558/1490305643087-S5RU5BHLNGP0BZZAZ6AH/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kPZjswWEEM1xUlE2nw_1gDZZw-zPPgdn4jUwVcJE1ZvWEtT5uBSRWt4vQZAgTJucoTqqXjS3CfNDSuuf31e0tVFEypcWtVdAnmHnO4a1hPNGKftICS8WvBaaDvL8dARr2lYCOBSuh7_iz0ZUXSA5sds/image-asset.jpeg" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/54028565e4b079634bac0558/1490305643087-S5RU5BHLNGP0BZZAZ6AH/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kPZjswWEEM1xUlE2nw_1gDZZw-zPPgdn4jUwVcJE1ZvWEtT5uBSRWt4vQZAgTJucoTqqXjS3CfNDSuuf31e0tVFEypcWtVdAnmHnO4a1hPNGKftICS8WvBaaDvL8dARr2lYCOBSuh7_iz0ZUXSA5sds/image-asset.jpeg" data-image-dimensions="450x300" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" data-image-id="58d4426abf629a6b1ddf35da" data-type="image" />
          </div>
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    </div>
  


  


</div></div><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html" data-block-type="2" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1490071600107_292239"><div class="sqs-block-content"><h3>IRON BUDDHA OOLONG TEA 25GRAMS&nbsp;</h3><p>This tea harvested from a small group of 35 years old Iron Buddha cultivar trees. Originally, the farmer only planted them for fun and picked the leaves for practicing. Fast forward to today, these rare original cultivars are high in demand and so the farmer teamed up with experienced Iron Buddha makers in Maokong to produce this truly old school Iron Buddhas. The tea is roasted to perfection with everlasting tea leaves that just does not stop giving. &nbsp;</p><p>Tasting Notes: Starts with a tint of roasted nut aroma then develops into a floral, chocolatey, woody notes with a medium dry aftertaste.&nbsp;<br />Brewing: 3grams, 90-95C, 150ml, 6 brews, 1-5minutes, blanching required<br />Varietal: Iron Buddha Oolong<br />Elevation: 500-600 m<br />Date: 2016 Spring&nbsp;</p><h3>AGED BAOZHONG OOLONG TEA 25GRAMS&nbsp;</h3><p>Some people recommend consuming baozhong (pouchong) teas within a year however, aging them develops amazing new characters. Aged for 25 years in the mountains, this tea’s flavours is like an interesting novel you can’t stop reading. &nbsp;</p><p>Tasting Notes: It starts with herbal flavours and minty finishes then develops sweet and almond characters leaving you wanting for more. &nbsp;<br />Brewing: 3grams, 90-95C, 150ml, 3 brews, 2-5minutes<br />Varietal: Qingxin Oolong<br />Elevation: 500-600m Harvest: 1989 Spring&nbsp;</p></div></div><div class="sqs-block image-block sqs-block-image" data-block-type="5" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1490071600107_295489"><div class="sqs-block-content">








  

    
  
    <div
        class="
          image-block-outer-wrapper
          layout-caption-below
          design-layout-inline
          
          
          
        "
        data-test="image-block-inline-outer-wrapper"
    >

      

      
        <figure
            class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
            style="max-width:100%;"
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          <div
              
                style="padding-bottom:66.81514739990234%;"
              
              class="
