          <figcaption class="image-caption-wrapper">
            <div class="image-caption"><p>Honey Scented black tea brewed.</p></div>
          </figcaption>
        
      
        </figure>
      

    </div>
  


  


</div></div><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html" data-block-type="2" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1490071600107_295689"><div class="sqs-block-content"><h3>HONEY SCENTED BLACK TEA 30GRAMS&nbsp;</h3><p>This new kind of black tea has become popular for summer production. During summer, there are more green grasshoppers that would munch on the tea leaves. This condition is less favourable for producing great Pouchongs but is perfect for making a cup of black teas with strong honey aroma and sweetness. &nbsp;</p><p>Tasting Notes: Strong honey aroma with orange brown liquid. The taste is sweet, smooth, easy drinking.&nbsp;<br />Brewing: 2.5grams, 90-95C, 150ml, 2 brews, 1-3minutes &nbsp;<br />Varietal: Qingxin oolong<br />Elevation: 500-600m<br />Harvest: 2016 Spring &nbsp;<br /> </p></div></div></div></div></div>
					
				
