			<p class="entry-categories">
				
			</p>
			<h1 data-content-field="title" class="entry-title">
				
					<a href="/teajournal/2016/9/7/recipe-honey-black-milk-tea-egg-pudding">Recipe | Honey Black Milk Tea Egg Pudding</a>
				
			</h1>

			<p class="entry-date-author">
				<span class="entry-author"><a href="/teajournal?author=54028563e4b09fa759f11482">Jenny Lo</a> · </span><time class="published" datetime="2016-09-07"><a href="/teajournal/2016/9/7/recipe-honey-black-milk-tea-egg-pudding">September  7, 2016</a></time>
			</p>

			<div class="entry-content">
				
					
						<div class="sqs-layout sqs-grid-12 columns-12" data-layout-label="Post Body" data-type="item" data-updated-on="1473282766871" id="item-57d07e519de4bbd9d3000f49"><div class="row sqs-row"><div class="col sqs-col-12 span-12"><div class="sqs-block image-block sqs-block-image" data-block-type="5" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1473240388383_118232"><div class="sqs-block-content">







 

  
  
    <div
        class="
          image-block-outer-wrapper
          layout-caption-below
          design-layout-inline
          
          
          
        "
        data-test="image-block-inline-outer-wrapper"
    >

      

      
        <figure
            class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
            style="max-width:2500.0px;"
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          <div
              
                style="padding-bottom:66.95999908447266%;"
              
              class="
                image-block-wrapper
                
          
        
                has-aspect-ratio
              "
              data-animation-role="image"
              
  data-animation-override

          >
            <noscript><img src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/54028565e4b079634bac0558/1473282898660-BWCC0IV5I8ADKI22NQYQ/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kPhE_b-FKx_EcxRx4teFEVN7gQa3H78H3Y0txjaiv_0fDoOvxcdMmMKkDsyUqMSsMWxHk725yiiHCCLfrh8O1z4YTzHvnKhyp6Da-NYroOW3ZGjoBKy3azqku80C789l0k5fwC0WRNFJBIXiBeNI5fL8LmMajxsBXeYxVzkYts3ds68Ud4HgM4ArFxmxGpI5hQ/image-asset.jpeg" alt="" /></noscript><img class="thumb-image" data-src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/54028565e4b079634bac0558/1473282898660-BWCC0IV5I8ADKI22NQYQ/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kPhE_b-FKx_EcxRx4teFEVN7gQa3H78H3Y0txjaiv_0fDoOvxcdMmMKkDsyUqMSsMWxHk725yiiHCCLfrh8O1z4YTzHvnKhyp6Da-NYroOW3ZGjoBKy3azqku80C789l0k5fwC0WRNFJBIXiBeNI5fL8LmMajxsBXeYxVzkYts3ds68Ud4HgM4ArFxmxGpI5hQ/image-asset.jpeg" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/54028565e4b079634bac0558/1473282898660-BWCC0IV5I8ADKI22NQYQ/ke17ZwdGBToddI8pDm48kPhE_b-FKx_EcxRx4teFEVN7gQa3H78H3Y0txjaiv_0fDoOvxcdMmMKkDsyUqMSsMWxHk725yiiHCCLfrh8O1z4YTzHvnKhyp6Da-NYroOW3ZGjoBKy3azqku80C789l0k5fwC0WRNFJBIXiBeNI5fL8LmMajxsBXeYxVzkYts3ds68Ud4HgM4ArFxmxGpI5hQ/image-asset.jpeg" data-image-dimensions="2500x1674" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" data-image-id="57d07eecd1758ee6334bb6d4" data-type="image" />
          </div>
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    </div>
  



</div></div><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html" data-block-type="2" id="block-7b3f6875aec221cc47d6"><div class="sqs-block-content"><h3>Honey Black Milk Tea Egg Pudding</h3><p>We looooove egg pudding, the japanese style with caramel on the bottom. Yum. The creamy milky pudding (some people call it flan) with the sweet bitter caramel. It's to die for.&nbsp;</p><p>Ingredients<br />white sugar 3tbsp, water 2tbsp, hot water 2tbsp<br />egg 2, milk 250ml, 150 whip cream, <a href="/blacktea?tag=honeyscent">honey black tea</a> 3grams,&nbsp;white sugar 2tbsp<br />makes 4 servings</p><p>Steps<br />1. Combine white sugar with water in a pot on medium heat, heat till golden colour then turn off heat and add hot water to make caramel. Quickly pour the caramel in 150ml oven bake cups.<br />2. Heat milk, whip cream,&nbsp;honey black tea and sugar in a pot on low heat until combined then take off heat.<br />3. Beat eggs together then add in mixture from step 2 using a sift.<br />4. Pour combine mixture into oven bake cups then rest in water bath tray. Put in oven for 25~35 minutes at 350F.&nbsp;<br />5. Take out of oven and chill before serving. ENJOY!<br /> </p></div></div><div class="row sqs-row"><div class="col sqs-col-6 span-6"><div class="sqs-block image-block sqs-block-image" data-block-type="5" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1473240388383_121551"><div class="sqs-block-content">







 

  
  
