          </div>
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    </div>
  



</div></div></div></div><div class="sqs-block html-block sqs-block-html" data-block-type="2" id="block-yui_3_17_2_1_1472175228677_781358"><div class="sqs-block-content"><p>Elements for making a good tea isn't just the elevation, picking only young buds or drinking them fresh within 3 months. It begins from the classical 5 elements;&nbsp;earth, water, air, fire, and aether and extending to the works of everyone involved from trimming, weeding, picking, processing to the final stage of storage. Understand it like planting vegetables and growing trees and making jam, every element involves the other;&nbsp;it's a cycle of nature!</p><p> </p></div></div></div></div></div>
					
				
